verbose_text: When a cell has inadequate oxygen supply, it produces a hypoxia induced factor (HIF, ie, transcriptional factor) to stimulate the release of endothelial growth factor-A (VEGF-A) which in turn binds to VEGF-A receptors on endothelial cells, activating a tyrosine kinase signaling pathway responsible for vasculogenesis.
